The paper discusses the optimization of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for ultra-low power Internet of Things end-nodes, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of computer vision (cs.CV), embedded systems (cs.ET), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), or electromagnetics (cs.EM). Additionally, the paper focuses on the architecture of an accelerator for binary-weight CNNs, which could fall under the sub-category of architecture (cs.AR).
